Hi everyone! So, here is a quick recap on our family trip to Kauai. First of all, the view in Kauai is very beautiful! As you are driving on the road, you will see the most gorgeous view of the mountain and trees. The mountain and trees make you feel like you are in a movie. Secondly, I really enjoy the peacefulness of the island. As the sun sets, you won't see a lot of activities happening unless you are at the resort. Therefore, if you are looking to party hard in Kauai, this is the wrong location for you. Kauai is mainly for families or couples who just want to relax without too many noises. The third thing about my trip is the food. I really enjoy some of the local food more than the resort food. However, finding food in Kauai can be a bit tricky because some of the restaurants are just randomly in the middle of nowhere, which I find exciting. Above all, this trip has been very memorable for our family. This is the kind of trip that makes me want to go back home to work harder so we can do this as a family again. Today, we are not saying goodbye to Kauai, but we are saying, "See You Later"! Aloha and Mahalo!

After coming over to America at the age of 7, my birthday was just another day. There was no party, no cakes, no friends. But I was not sad about it because I knew the circumstances were different. I knew the struggle was real when I saw 6 of us brothers and sisters sleeping in one room, but there’s always joy and laughter. Throughout the years, I don’t really talk or mention anything about my birthday because it just another day to me. But today is different, today is not just another day. Today is special because without today Minh aka The Thai Lyfe would not exist and NO ONE WOULD MAKE YOU LAUGH, and BRIGHT UP YOUR DAY.
